 "Hatano-Nelson Model",
 "\[NonBreakingSpace]\[NonBreakingSpace]",
 Cell["(3)", "ExampleCount",ExpressionUUID->
  "b07024a3-ae0c-4a39-a82c-8a1eae7bd8b3"]
}], "ExampleSubsection", "ExampleSubsection",
 WholeCellGroupOpener->True,
 CacheGraphics->False,
 CellID->395109648,ExpressionUUID->"073ed872-2e63-4b82-9c5e-23c2fb4d07ca"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The ",
 StyleBox["Hatano",
  IgnoreSpellCheck->True,
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox["-Nelson model",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is a non-Hermitian Hamiltonian model of fermionic modes exhibiting the \
so-called ",
 StyleBox["skin effect",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". It was introduced by  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData[
      StyleBox[{
        StyleBox["Hatano", IgnoreSpellCheck -> True], 
        " and Nelson in 1996"}]]], 
    "https://doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevLett.77.570"},
   "WebLink",
   BaseStyle->{"TechNoteText"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "39d45af0-19cf-4388-a9ce-bbd49c108711"],
 ", originally, in the context of localization transitions, and later applied \
to describe vortex pinning in superconductors ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData[
      StyleBox[{"(", 
        StyleBox["Hatano", IgnoreSpellCheck -> True], 
        " and Nelson, 1997)"}]]], "https://doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevB.56.8651"},
   
   "WebLink",
   BaseStyle->{"TechNoteText"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cf2312f4-fb22-4748-84f9-fe5ea5fe74cf"],
 ". The non-hermicity and associated skin effect come from quantum \
dissipative processes through a coupling to the bath ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData[
      StyleBox[{"(Kawabata, ", 
        StyleBox["Numasawa", IgnoreSpellCheck -> True], " and ", 
        StyleBox["Ryu", IgnoreSpellCheck -> True], ", 2023)"}]]], 
    "https://doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevX.13.021007"},
   "WebLink",
   BaseStyle->{"TechNoteText"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a10f6bcd-e3c5-4da8-a4a8-d0de8cdff90b"],
 "."
}], "ExampleText",
 CellID->84723117,ExpressionUUID->"778c9759-9b29-4d5c-9cdf-c26fec0b59aa"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Here, we consider a ",
 StyleBox["projective model",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " for the ",
 StyleBox["Hatano",
  IgnoreSpellCheck->True],
 "-Nelson Hamiltonian, where the non-Hermitian terms come from the projective \
quantum jump operators. These projective quantum jump operators may be \
described by using ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["BravyiMeasurement"]], 
    "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/BravyiMeasurement", "QuantumMob Package Symbol"},
   "PackageLink",
   BaseStyle->"InlineFormula"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "5a8c02db-44eb-49ef-b199-a143312934ad"],
 "."
}], "ExampleText",
 CellID->2002068658,ExpressionUUID->"aede682a-84dd-4609-a01e-9f712ad519ad"],

Cell["Set the number of fermion modes:", "ExampleText",
 CellID->1251699765,ExpressionUUID->"d14a49c6-99c3-4d47-89a4-40cde28f661f"],

